:: StoryStylesheet [stylesheet]
/*
	Twine Story Styles

	Simple CSS Template to help Twine authors change
		the default appearance

	This stylesheet combines the organizational structure of the Twine CSS Template
	with the design elements from the Harlowe Template, featuring:
	- Libre Baskerville serif font for a literary feel
	- Light & dark theme that follows system preferences
	- Responsive layout with sidebar repositioning
	- Clean, readable design optimized for storytelling

	Based on:
	- Twine CSS Template - https://github.com/danieltalsky/twine-css-template
	  by Daniel Talsky <daniel@danieltalsky.com>
	- Harlowe Template by Michael Verdi (https://verdi.space)

	Special thanks to furkle's Twine 2 Harlowe CSS Tutorial
	no longer up on the web but helped a lot with the basics.

	COLORS

	All color definitions are at the end of this file in the COLOR THEMES section.
	Light theme is default; dark theme activates when the user's system prefers dark mode.
	Change them to make your story have whatever mood you want, just make sure it's readable!

	FONTS

	This template uses Libre Baskerville, a classic serif font optimized for
	web reading and storytelling. You can pick any combination of Google fonts
	at https://fonts.google.com/ and they will generate the import line for you.
*/
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Baskerville:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap');

/* Default options for the entire browser window */
tw-story {
	display: block;
	width: 90vw; /* 90% viewport width on small screens, limited by max-width on large */
	margin: auto;
	padding: 2rem 0 8rem; /* Extra bottom padding for sidebar on small screens */
	overflow: visible;
	font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', Georgia, serif;
	font-weight: 400;
	font-size: 1.15rem;
	line-height: 1.75rem; /* Comfortable spacing for reading */
}

b, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
	font-weight: 700;
}

h1:first-of-type {
	margin: 0 0 0.6em 0; /* Remove top margin - comment out if undesired */
}

tw-passage {
	width: 100%; /* Full width within tw-story container */
}

/* Sidebar with back/forward buttons - positioned at bottom on small screens */
tw-sidebar {
	text-align: left;
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: min-content min-content;
	width: min-content;
	grid-gap: 1rem;
	position: absolute;
	bottom: -5rem;
	/* display: none; */ /* Uncomment to hide sidebar */
}

/* Navigation icons within sidebar - scoped to avoid affecting other tw-icon elements */
tw-sidebar tw-icon {
	opacity: 1 !important;
	margin: 0 0 1rem;
	font-size: 3rem;
}

tw-sidebar tw-icon:hover {
	opacity: 1 !important;
}

/*
  LINK STYLES

  NOTE: Colors are defined in COLOR THEMES section below.
*/
.enchantment-link, tw-link, a {
	font-weight: normal;
	text-decoration: underline;
	transition: color 0.2s ease;
}

/*
	EFFECTS

	Pulse-in effect for dynamically appearing text. Usage:
	<span class="pulse-in">Text that gets shown.</span>

	NOTE: Animation colors defined in COLOR THEMES section below.
*/
.pulse-in {
	animation: pulsein 1.2s linear 3;
}

span.pulse-in {
	font-size: inherit;
}

/* IMAGE STYLES */

img {
	max-width: 100%;
	height: auto; /* Maintains aspect ratio */
}

img.full-width {
	display: block;
	margin-right: auto;
	margin-left: auto;
	width: 100%;
}

/*
	RESPONSIVE DESIGN

	Breakpoints:
	- Below 576px: Phones (sidebar at bottom)
	- 576px-1099px: Tablets (sidebar at bottom-right)
	- 1100px and up: Desktop (sidebar left, max-width 800px)
*/

@media (min-width: 576px) {
	tw-story {
		padding: 2rem 0;
	}

	tw-sidebar {
		left: unset;
		width: min-content;
		position: absolute;
	}
}

@media (min-width: 1100px) {
	tw-story {
		max-width: 800px; /* ~55-60 chars per line for readability */
		font-size: 1.3rem;
		line-height: 1.9rem;
	}

	tw-sidebar {
		position: absolute;
		left: -8rem; /* Positioned outside main content */
		width: min-content;
		bottom: initial;
	}
}

